that%20generate%20demand%20for%20military%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20making%20some%20sectors%20winners%20in%20Russia's%20wartime%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20trade%20jumped%20by%20nearly%207%25%20last%20year%2C%20while%20activities%20in%20the%20financial%20sector%20and%20construction%20grew%20by%206.6%25%20and%203.6%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20boosted%20Russia's%20real%20GDP%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20economic%20growth%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%20%E2%80%94%20by%203.6%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20development%20has%20made%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-ukraine-war-winners-wealth-redistribution-social-mobility-putin-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoor%20Russians%20better%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20financially%2C%20complicating%20any%20calculus%20over%20how%20to%20end%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a5dbd017-74b6-498a-a515-a868703de10b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20World%20Bank%20upgraded%20seven%20countries%2C%20downgraded%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20Russia%2C%20the%20World%20Bank%20also%20upgraded%20Bulgaria%20and%20Palau%20from%20upper-middle-income%20to%20high-income%20countries.%20Their%20upgrades%20came%20after%20several%20years%20of%20post-pandemic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20also%20moved%20up%20from%20a%20lower-middle-income%20country%20to%20upper-middle-income%20country%20as%20real%20GDP%20grew%205.3%25%20%E2%80%94%20reversing%20a%20steep%2028.8%25%20slump%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20Ukraine's%20economy%20was%20significantly%20impaired%20by%20Russia's%20invasion%2C%20real%20growth%20in%202023%20was%20driven%20by%20construction%20activity%20(24.6%25)%2C%20reflecting%20a%20sizable%20increase%20in%20investment%20spending%20(52.9%25)%20supporting%20Ukraine's%20reconstruction%20effort%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20ongoing%20destruction%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20World%20Bank%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a