20decide%20if%20the%20SCOTUS%20ruling%20%26quot%3Bwould%20require%20a%20reversal%20or%20modification%20of%20the%20judgment%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20law%20by%20an%20appellate%20court.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20come%20down%20to%20two%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michel%20Paradis%2C%20an%20attorney%20who%20teaches%20national%20security%20and%20constitutional%20law%20at%20Columbia%20Law%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWas%20the%20evidence%20or%20testimony%20%26quot%3Bofficial%20in%20some%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20therefore%20subject%20to%20this%20new%20immunity%20rule%3F%20And%20if%20so%2C%20was%20its%20use%20at%20trial%20%26quot%3Ba%20harmless%20error.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20Merchan%20and%20New%20York's%20appellate%20courts%20uphold%20Trump's%20conviction%20%E2%80%94%20Trump%20could%20just%20make%20a%20return%20trip%20to%20SCOTUS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20new%20sentencing%20date%20will%20be%20September%2018%2C%20Merchan%20ruled%20%E2%80%94%20if%20sentencing%20is%20%26quot%3Bstill%20necessary%26quot%3B%20by%20that%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2251ac0e06-a0e0-45dd-a5c2-55464212bad5%5C%22%3EWhy%20People's%2081%20may%20be%20Trump's%20best%20monkey-wrench%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20hopes%20of%20setting%20aside%20Trump's%20verdict%2C%20Trump's%20lawyers%20raised%20other%20instances%20where%20they%20say%20%26quot%3Bofficial%20acts%26quot%3B%20were%20improperly%20used%20at%20trial%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20one%20is%20testimony%20by%20Trump's%20former%20communications%20director%2C%20Hicks%2C%20who%20described%20to%20jurors%20Trump's%20reaction%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%2C%20when%20news%20of%20Trump's%20hush-money%20payment%20to%20porn%20star%20Stormy%20Daniels%20first%20broke%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20wanted%20to%20know%20how%20it%20was%20playing%2C%26quot%3B%20Hicks%20told%20the%20jury%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20news%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20Mr.%20Trump's%20opinion%20was%20it%20was%20better%20to%20be%20dealing%20with%20it%20now%2C%20and%20that%20it%20would%20have%20been%20bad%20to%20have%20that%20story%20come%20out%20before%20the%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20jurors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20devastating%2C%26quot%3B%20Steinglass%2C%20the%20prosecutor%2C%20said%20in%20closing%20arguments%20of%20Hick's%20testimony%2C%20noting%20that%20it%20firmly%20linked%20the%20hush-money%20payment%20to%20the%20presidential%20election%2C%20a%20legally-vital%20connection%20Trump%20had%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParadis%20said%20prosecutors%20may%20now%20find%20themselves%20battling%20with%20the%20defense%20over%20how%20much%20of%20Hicks'%20Oval%20Office%20conversation%20with%20Trump%20concerned%20an%20official%20topic%2C%20and%20must%20therefore%20be%20banned%20as%20testimony.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20as%20is%20more%20likely%2C%20appeals%20judges%20down%20the%20line%20%E2%80%94%20may%20bar%20any%20prosecutorial%20use%20of%20the%20Hicks-Trump%20conversation%20merely%20because%20some%20of%20it%20could%20have%20touched%20on%20official%20acts%2C%20Paradis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20is%20also%20signaling%20that%20it%20will%20challenge%20the%20use%20of%20certain%20incriminating%20tweets%2C%20including%20one%20from%20May%2C%202018%2C%20in%20which%20Trump%20again%20referred%20to%20his%20payments%20to%20Cohen%20as%20%26quot%3Breimbursement%26quot%3B%20for%20%26quot%3Ba%20non-disclosure%20agreement%2C%26quot%3B%20AKA%20hush%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20May%202018%20tweet%20by%20then-President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20in%20which%20he%20acknowledges%20that%20Michael%20Cohen%20received%20%26quot%3Breimbursement%26quot%3B%20for%20%20a%20%26quot%3Bnon-disclosure%20agreement.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664fdef3a961b37edf398b44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22658%5C%22%3E%3Cfigc