rotections%20for%20soldiers%2C%20built%20from%20within%20instead%20of%20adding%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22M1A2%20Abrams%20tank%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63652703ff27460018ed9cf5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20M1A2%20Abrams%20at%20the%20Army%20Armor%20School%20at%20Fort%20Benning%20in%20Georgia%20on%20April%2029%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%2FSpc.%20Joshua%20Taeckens%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20end%2C%20the%20Army%20is%20asking%20for%20%24246%20million%20for%20the%20next%20fiscal%20year%2C%20with%20plans%20to%20spend%20another%20%24366%20million%20on%20tank%20upgrades%20in%20fiscal%202026.%20A%20paper%20developed%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FIF%2FIF12495%2F2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECongressional%20Research%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%20lays%20out%20the%20Army's%20primary%20objectives%20for%20modernization.%20It%20cites%20a%202019%20Army%20Science%20Board%20study%20that%20reportedly%20influenced%20the%20path%20the%20service%20is%20currently%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20them%20would%20merely%20adopt%20technologies%20already%20in%20use%20by%20other%20premier%20tanks%2C%20such%20as%20an%20autoloader%2C%20which%20might%20allow%20the%20Abrams%20to%20employ%20a%20crew%20of%20three%20instead%20of%20four%20and%20cut%20down%20on%20manpower.%20The%20French%20Leclerc%20and%20South%20Korean%20K2%20Black%20Panther%20already%20have%20autoloaders%2C%20as%20do%20Russian%2C%20Japanese%2C%20and%20Chinese%20tanks.%20Also%20proposed%20is%20a%20new%20main%20gun%20in%20lieu%20of%20the%20Abrams'%20legacy%20120mm%20L%2F44%20M256%20smoothbore%20armament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20proposed%20features%20would%20enhance%20the%20Abrams'%20stealth%3B%20these%20include%20%26quot%3Bmasking%26quot%3B%20tech%20that